1138/// printInstruction - This method is automatically generated by tablegen
1139/// from the instruction set description.
1140void SparcInstPrinter::printInstruction(const MCInst *MI, uint64_t Address, const MCSubtargetInfo &STI, raw_ostream &O) {
1141 O << "\t";
1142
1143 auto MnemonicInfo = getMnemonic(MI);
1144
1145 O << MnemonicInfo.first;
1146
1147 uint32_t Bits = MnemonicInfo.second;
1148 assert(Bits != 0 && "Cannot print this instruction.");
1149
1150 // Fragment 0 encoded into 4 bits for 13 unique commands.
1151 switch ((Bits >> 12) & 15) {
1152 default: llvm_unreachable("Invalid command number.");
1153 case 0:
1154 // DBG_VALUE, DBG_INSTR_REF, DBG_LABEL, BUNDLE, LIFETIME_START, LIFETIME_...
1155 return;
1156 break;
1157 case 1:
1158 // ADJCALLSTACKDOWN, ADJCALLSTACKUP, BA, BPGEZapn, BPGEZapt, BPGEZnapn, B...
1159 printOperand(MI, 0, STI, O);
1160 break;
1161 case 2:
1162 // GETPCX
1163 printGetPCX(MI, 0, STI, O);
1164 return;
1165 break;
1166 case 3:
1167 // SET, ADDCCri, ADDCCrr, ADDCri, ADDCrr, ADDEri, ADDErr, ADDXC, ADDXCCC,...
1168 printOperand(MI, 1, STI, O);
1169 break;
1170 case 4:
1171 // BCOND, BCONDA, BPFCC, BPFCCA, BPFCCANT, BPFCCNT, BPICC, BPICCA, BPICCA...
1172 printCCOperand(MI, 1, STI, O);
1173 break;
1174 case 5:
1175 // BINDri, BINDrr, CALLri, CALLrr, FLUSHri, FLUSHrr, LDCSRri, LDCSRrr, LD...
1176 printMemOperand(MI, 0, STI, O);
1177 break;
1178 case 6:
1179 // FMOVD_FCC, FMOVD_ICC, FMOVD_XCC, FMOVQ_FCC, FMOVQ_ICC, FMOVQ_XCC, FMOV...
1180 printCCOperand(MI, 3, STI, O);
1181 break;
1182 case 7:
1183 // JMPLri, JMPLrr, LDArr, LDCri, LDCrr, LDDArr, LDDCri, LDDCrr, LDDFArr, ...
1184 printMemOperand(MI, 1, STI, O);
1185 break;
1186 case 8:
1187 // LEAX_ADDri, LEA_ADDri
1188 printMemOperand(MI, 1, STI, O, "arith");
1189 O << ", ";
1190 printOperand(MI, 0, STI, O);
1191 return;
1192 break;
1193 case 9:
1194 // MEMBARi
1195 printMembarTag(MI, 0, STI, O);
1196 return;
1197 break;
1198 case 10:
1199 // STArr, STBArr, STBri, STBrr, STCri, STCrr, STDArr, STDCri, STDCrr, STD...
1200 printOperand(MI, 2, STI, O);
1201 O << ", [";
1202 printMemOperand(MI, 0, STI, O);
1203 break;
1204 case 11:
1205 // TICCri, TICCrr, TRAPri, TRAPrr, TXCCri, TXCCrr
1206 printCCOperand(MI, 2, STI, O);
1207 break;
1208 case 12:
1209 // V9FMOVD_FCC, V9FMOVQ_FCC, V9FMOVS_FCC, V9MOVFCCri, V9MOVFCCrr
1210 printCCOperand(MI, 4, STI, O);
1211 O << ' ';
1212 printOperand(MI, 1, STI, O);
1213 O << ", ";
1214 printOperand(MI, 2, STI, O);
1215 O << ", ";
1216 printOperand(MI, 0, STI, O);
1217 return;
1218 break;
1219 }
1220
1221
1222 // Fragment 1 encoded into 5 bits for 21 unique commands.
1223 switch ((Bits >> 16) & 31) {
1224 default: llvm_unreachable("Invalid command number.");
1225 case 0:
1226 // ADJCALLSTACKDOWN, SET, ADDCCri, ADDCCrr, ADDCri, ADDCrr, ADDEri, ADDEr...
1227 O << ", ";
1228 break;
1229 case 1:
1230 // ADJCALLSTACKUP, BA, BINDri, BINDrr, CALL, CALLri, CALLrr, CMASK16, CMA...
1231 return;
1232 break;
1233 case 2:
1234 // BCOND, BPFCC, CBCOND, FBCOND, TRAPri, TRAPrr
1235 O << ' ';
1236 break;
1237 case 3:
1238 // BCONDA, BPFCCA, CBCONDA, FBCONDA
1239 O << ",a ";
1240 break;
1241 case 4:
1242 // BPFCCANT
1243 O << ",a,pn ";
1244 printOperand(MI, 2, STI, O);
1245 O << ", ";
1246 printOperand(MI, 0, STI, O);
1247 return;
1248 break;
1249 case 5:
1250 // BPFCCNT
1251 O << ",pn ";
1252 printOperand(MI, 2, STI, O);
1253 O << ", ";
1254 printOperand(MI, 0, STI, O);
1255 return;
1256 break;
1257 case 6:
1258 // BPICC, FMOVD_ICC, FMOVQ_ICC, FMOVS_ICC, MOVICCri, MOVICCrr, TICCri, TI...
1259 O << " %icc, ";
1260 break;
1261 case 7:
1262 // BPICCA
1263 O << ",a %icc, ";
1264 printOperand(MI, 0, STI, O);
1265 return;
1266 break;
1267 case 8:
1268 // BPICCANT
1269 O << ",a,pn %icc, ";
1270 printOperand(MI, 0, STI, O);
1271 return;
1272 break;
1273 case 9:
1274 // BPICCNT
1275 O << ",pn %icc, ";
1276 printOperand(MI, 0, STI, O);
1277 return;
1278 break;
1279 case 10:
1280 // BPXCC, FMOVD_XCC, FMOVQ_XCC, FMOVS_XCC, MOVXCCri, MOVXCCrr, TXCCri, TX...
1281 O << " %xcc, ";
1282 break;
1283 case 11:
1284 // BPXCCA
1285 O << ",a %xcc, ";
1286 printOperand(MI, 0, STI, O);
1287 return;
1288 break;
1289 case 12:
1290 // BPXCCANT
1291 O << ",a,pn %xcc, ";
1292 printOperand(MI, 0, STI, O);
1293 return;
1294 break;
1295 case 13:
1296 // BPXCCNT
1297 O << ",pn %xcc, ";
1298 printOperand(MI, 0, STI, O);
1299 return;
1300 break;
1301 case 14:
1302 // CASAasi10
1303 O << "] 10, ";
1304 printOperand(MI, 2, STI, O);
1305 O << ", ";
1306 printOperand(MI, 0, STI, O);
1307 return;
1308 break;
1309 case 15:
1310 // CASArr, LDArr, LDDArr, LDDFArr, LDFArr, LDQFArr, LDSBArr, LDSHArr, LDS...
1311 O << "] ";
1312 break;
1313 case 16:
1314 // CASXrr, CASrr, LDCri, LDCrr, LDDCri, LDDCrr, LDDFri, LDDFrr, LDDri, LD...
1315 O << "], ";
1316 break;
1317 case 17:
1318 // FMOVD_FCC, FMOVQ_FCC, FMOVS_FCC, MOVFCCri, MOVFCCrr
1319 O << " %fcc0, ";
1320 printOperand(MI, 1, STI, O);
1321 O << ", ";
1322 printOperand(MI, 0, STI, O);
1323 return;
1324 break;
1325 case 18:
1326 // LDCSRri, LDCSRrr
1327 O << "], %csr";
1328 return;
1329 break;
1330 case 19:
1331 // LDFSRri, LDFSRrr, LDXFSRri, LDXFSRrr
1332 O << "], %fsr";
1333 return;
1334 break;
1335 case 20:
1336 // STBri, STBrr, STCSRri, STCSRrr, STCri, STCrr, STDCQri, STDCQrr, STDCri...
1337 O << ']';
1338 return;
1339 break;
1340 }
1341
1342
1343 // Fragment 2 encoded into 3 bits for 5 unique commands.
1344 switch ((Bits >> 21) & 7) {
1345 default: llvm_unreachable("Invalid command number.");
1346 case 0:
1347 // ADJCALLSTACKDOWN, BPGEZapn, BPGEZapt, BPGEZnapn, BPGEZnapt, BPGZapn, B...
1348 printOperand(MI, 1, STI, O);
1349 break;
1350 case 1:
1351 // SET, BCOND, BCONDA, BPICC, BPXCC, CBCOND, CBCONDA, FABSD, FABSQ, FABSS...
1352 printOperand(MI, 0, STI, O);
1353 break;
1354 case 2:
1355 // ADDCCri, ADDCCrr, ADDCri, ADDCrr, ADDEri, ADDErr, ADDXC, ADDXCCC, ADDX...
1356 printOperand(MI, 2, STI, O);
1357 O << ", ";
1358 printOperand(MI, 0, STI, O);
1359 break;
1360 case 3:
1361 // CASArr
1362 printOperand(MI, 4, STI, O);
1363 O << ", ";
1364 printOperand(MI, 2, STI, O);
1365 O << ", ";
1366 printOperand(MI, 0, STI, O);
1367 return;
1368 break;
1369 case 4:
1370 // LDArr, LDDArr, LDDFArr, LDFArr, LDQFArr, LDSBArr, LDSHArr, LDSTUBArr, ...
1371 printOperand(MI, 3, STI, O);
1372 break;
1373 }
1374
1375
1376 // Fragment 3 encoded into 3 bits for 6 unique commands.
1377 switch ((Bits >> 24) & 7) {
1378 default: llvm_unreachable("Invalid command number.");
1379 case 0:
1380 // ADJCALLSTACKDOWN, SET, ADDCCri, ADDCCrr, ADDCri, ADDCrr, ADDEri, ADDEr...
1381 return;
1382 break;
1383 case 1:
1384 // FLCMPD, FLCMPS, FMOVD_ICC, FMOVD_XCC, FMOVQ_ICC, FMOVQ_XCC, FMOVS_ICC,...
1385 O << ", ";
1386 break;
1387 case 2:
1388 // PWRPSRri, PWRPSRrr, WRPSRri, WRPSRrr
1389 O << ", %psr";
1390 return;
1391 break;
1392 case 3:
1393 // TICCri, TICCrr, TRAPri, TRAPrr, TXCCri, TXCCrr
1394 O << " + ";
1395 printOperand(MI, 1, STI, O);
1396 return;
1397 break;
1398 case 4:
1399 // WRTBRri, WRTBRrr
1400 O << ", %tbr";
1401 return;
1402 break;
1403 case 5:
1404 // WRWIMri, WRWIMrr
1405 O << ", %wim";
1406 return;
1407 break;
1408 }
1409
1410
1411 // Fragment 4 encoded into 2 bits for 3 unique commands.
1412 switch ((Bits >> 27) & 3) {
1413 default: llvm_unreachable("Invalid command number.");
1414 case 0:
1415 // FLCMPD, FLCMPS, V9FCMPD, V9FCMPED, V9FCMPEQ, V9FCMPES, V9FCMPQ, V9FCMP...
1416 printOperand(MI, 2, STI, O);
1417 return;
1418 break;
1419 case 1:
1420 // FMOVD_ICC, FMOVD_XCC, FMOVQ_ICC, FMOVQ_XCC, FMOVS_ICC, FMOVS_XCC, LDAr...
1421 printOperand(MI, 0, STI, O);
1422 return;
1423 break;
1424 case 2:
1425 // TLS_ADDXrr, TLS_ADDrr, TLS_LDXrr, TLS_LDrr
1426 printOperand(MI, 3, STI, O);
1427 return;
1428 break;
1429 }
1430
1431}

5608#ifndef NDEBUG
5609 static struct SortCheck {
5610 SortCheck(ArrayRef<PatternsForOpcode> OpToPatterns) {
5611 assert(std::is_sorted(
5612 OpToPatterns.begin(), OpToPatterns.end(),
5613 [](const PatternsForOpcode &L, const PatternsForOpcode &R) {
5614 return L.Opcode < R.Opcode;
5615 }) &&
5616 "tablegen failed to sort opcode patterns");
5617 }
5618 } sortCheckVar(OpToPatterns);
5619#endif
5620
5621 AliasMatchingData M {
5622 makeArrayRef(OpToPatterns),
5623 makeArrayRef(Patterns),
5624 makeArrayRef(Conds),
5625 StringRef(AsmStrings, array_lengthof(AsmStrings)),
5626 nullptr,
5627 };
5628 const char *AsmString = matchAliasPatterns(MI, &STI, M);
5629 if (!AsmString) return false;
5630
5631 unsigned I = 0;
5632 while (AsmString[I] != ' ' && AsmString[I] != '\t' &&
5633 AsmString[I] != '$' && AsmString[I] != '\0')
5634 ++I;
5635 OS << '\t' << StringRef(AsmString, I);
5636 if (AsmString[I] != '\0') {
5637 if (AsmString[I] == ' ' || AsmString[I] == '\t') {
5638 OS << '\t';
5639 ++I;
5640 }
5641 do {
5642 if (AsmString[I] == '$') {
5643 ++I;
5644 if (AsmString[I] == (char)0xff) {
5645 ++I;
5646 int OpIdx = AsmString[I++] - 1;
5647 int PrintMethodIdx = AsmString[I++] - 1;
5648 printCustomAliasOperand(MI, Address, OpIdx, PrintMethodIdx, STI, OS);
5649 } else
5650 printOperand(MI, unsigned(AsmString[I++]) - 1, STI, OS);
5651 } else {
5652 OS << AsmString[I++];
5653 }
5654 } while (AsmString[I] != '\0');
5655 }
5656
5657 return true;
5658}

5662 unsigned PrintMethodIdx,
5663 const MCSubtargetInfo &STI,
5664 raw_ostream &OS) {
5665 llvm_unreachable("Unknown PrintMethod kind");
5666}
